name: God Don't Like Ugly
description:
Oblivious, strange malaise.
I lay with vertigo. Ad nauseum.
 
Tunneling,
The moon casts its shadow.
 
My roots, suspended –
Rot, spreading throughout.
 
With a hunger in my eyes,
Exposed to your barren landscape.
 
At most times,
I long to be normal.
 
Yet, I’m seeing twos and threes,
In delusions of grandeur.
 
Jaded from harsh realities;
I’ve become an island.
 
Wishing I was cut from the same cloth,
Experiencing in the ways that you do.
